%pyspark

from pyspark.sql.types import *

#Create Schema

schema = StructType([
    StructField("calldate", StringType(), True),
    StructField("accountcode", StringType(), True),
    StructField("src", StringType(), True),
    StructField("dst", StringType(), True),
    StructField("dst_number_len", StringType(), True),
    StructField("lastapp", StringType(), True),
    StructField("label", StringType(), True)
    ])
    
#Split the dataset into columns

cdr_data = cdr_data.map(lambda line: line.split(","))

dst = cdr_data.map(lambda x: x[3])
print(dst.take(30))

#Filter out calls to voicemail 
#cdr_data = cdr_data.filter(lambda x: '*' not in x[3] and 'vm' not in x[3] and 'hang' not in x[3] )

#Filter out calls that have at least 10 digits
cdr_data = cdr_data.filter(lambda x: len(x[3]) >= 10 and 'START' not in x[3] )

#Create a dataframe from the dataset

cdr_df = sqlContext.createDataFrame(cdr_data,schema)

#Register a table to represent the dataframe so that we can use SQL against it
sqlContext.registerDataFrameAsTable(cdr_df, "cdr")

#Print the schema to validate

cdr_df.printSchema()
